docs.abstract: A new law mandating that the state’s public companies have a minimum number of women on their boards could do more harm than good.

docs.lead_paragraph: For years, this column has highlighted the dearth of women on corporate boards and in executive positions. It has suggested all sorts of ways for investors and others to encourage — even force — more diversity on boards, and raised pointed questions about why there are so few women in those roles.
